==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*aluþ-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''alo-'' (Middle Dutch [[ale]]), Old High German ''al-'', Old Norse [[ǫl]] (Swedish [[öl]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'æalʊ/

===Noun===
'''ealu''' ''n''
# [[beer]], [[ale]]
#:''Ne he ealu ne drince næfre oððe win'': let him never drink beer nor wine.  (''Judges'')


